						<summary>

						<p>Hero-stone lying in the fort.</p>						

						<p>Sivachitta Vīra-Permāḍi 12th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly mutilated inscription dated • • • • • trayōdasi, Monday refers to Śivachitta Vajradēva and to a Kadamba king. It records the death of a hero in a great fight. Vijayamasāhaṇi, son of Rāya-sāhaṇi. Sōḍapa was a <hi rend="italic">ḍiṁgariga</hi> of Vajradēva.</p>						

						<p>The characters are of about 12th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
